The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Shah Rukh, Kareena to perform
                                                                                                                       7                                      Shah Rukh, Kareena to perform
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Shah Rukh Khan and Kareena Kapoor will perform at the second Sahara India Sports Awards in Mumbai on Saturday.         
	The Sports Journalists Federation of India members nominated the players for the awards.         
	The winners will be decided by a jury, headed by former India captain Sunil Gavaskar. Sachin Tendulkar and the Indian Davis Cup team are in the running for the top honours.         
	Tendulkar is among the nominees for the male Cricketer of the Year while Somdev Dev Varman and Co. are in contention for the Team of the Year, according to a statement on Friday..         
	The Sportsman of the Year would be a close contest between world champions Viswanathan Anand and Sushil Kumar.                                                                                                                     
